         WOO! Heh, I was just coming here to complain about the possible stealth nerf. Btw, to clear it up for those of you who didn't understand..</P><P>Prepatch, pet summoned was somewhere within a 5 level range. 59, 61, 63, 65 and 67 hitters (only dealing with EoT here for the moment).</P><P>With the Encyclopedia (our focus book), the max EoT would hit for 71.</P><P>Now, after this last patch, EoT is hitting for 63. Focused for 67.<BR>That friends, is a nerf. </P><P>Rich, the man I'm coming to love.. just confirmed that was not how it was meant to be. In the patch it stated our 'max' pet was to be summoned consistently now. Which means we were supposed to log on, and constantly summon a 67 (unfocused) or 71 (focused) EoT pet each and every time.  So, it was a messup, and they're gonna fix it. <BR>Be happy it'll be fixed, be sad it may take until PoP at the rate they patch sometimes. ;) (coughs, DoT stacking still an issue)</P><P>Rich, thanks for posting so quickly on this matter.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=205091" target="_blank"><font color=red><font size=5>Ashtaroth Solarium</font id=size5></font id=red></a><BR><i>Nec-Romancer of Innoruuk</i><BR><i>Legends of the Realm</i><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
